xbrlcore.dimensions
Class MultipleDimensionType

java.lang.Object
  xbrlcore.dimensions.MultipleDimensionType
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Cloneable
public class MultipleDimensionType
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Cloneable

This class represents a model of multiple dimension/domain member combinations.

Unlike a Hypercube, which represents one or multiple Dimensions with a set of domain members, this class represents one or multiple dimensions with only one specific domain member.

Author:
Daniel Hamm

addPredecessorDimensionDomain

public void addPredecessorDimensionDomain(MultipleDimensionType newMDT)
Adds all dimensions/domain member of a MultipleDimensionType object (including current and previous ones) to the previous dimensions/domain member of this MultipleDimensionType.

Example:
This object contains of Dimension d1 with domain member m1 and Dimension d2 with domain member m2: d1m1, d2m2. If newMDT consists of Dimension d3 with domain member m3 and Dimension d4 with domain member m4, after invoking this method this object contains of d1m1, d2m2, d3m3, d4m4 whereas d1m1 still is the "current" dimenson / domain member combination.

Parameters:
newMDT - The MultipleDimensionType object whose elements shall be added to this object.

equals

public boolean equals(java.lang.Object obj)
This method checks if two objects of MultipleDimensionType are "equal". This is true if
- both refer to the same "current" dimension/domain and
- if also all the predecessor dimension/domain member combinations are the same (the order of the previous dimension / domain member combinations is not taken into account).

Overrides:
equals in class java.lang.Object
Returns:
True if both objects are equal, false otherwise.
